<subSubSection pageId="71" pageNumber="72" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="71.[151,1436,987,1804]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1671,1696]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zelazny &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2011" box="[330,506,1672,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aperta">
<emphasis box="[330,506,1672,1696]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Rhotana aperta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows some similarities to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zelazny &amp; Webb, 2011" authorityName="Zelazny &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2011" box="[826,962,1672,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribraria" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[826,962,1672,1696]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">R. cribraria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[971,1062,1672,1695]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, also found in Borneo, and to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zelazny" authorityName="Zelazny &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torrevillasi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">R. torrevillasi</emphasis>
Zelazny
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[480,610,1708,1732]" name="Philippines" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Philippines</collectingCountry>
. It can be recognized by the hindwings having a conspicuous brown mark with a round opening, by the basal parts of Sc, R, and M on the forewings being light brown, and by the male aedeagus having a pointed tip and lacking a lateral pointed process near its end.
</paragraph>
